n to control appears less of an issue in experimental literature ( Falk \& Kosfeld; Burdin et al.) P-A game. P sets lower bound on work =={\textgreater} lower contributions. When 3rd party sets lower bound then no deterioration visible. Deliberative vs. affective cognitive system. Deliberative system reveals concern for others. Affective systems id driven toward whatever depending on degree of sympathy triggered (Loewenstein \& O'Donoghue) Allowing punishment can have a variety of consequences. Only works when viewed as legitimate and target has clearly violated norms. Tension/trilemma between incentives and not undermining moral orders. Andreoni \& Miller 2001 World According to GARP.},
